title: Establishes public policy that no antenuptial agreement shall become binding for 30 days during which period either party thereto may withdraw upon notice to other
actClause: AN ACT to amend the general obligations law and the domestic relations law, in relation to establishing the public policy of the state that no antenuptial agreement become binding for thirty days during which period either party may withdraw upon written notice to the other and requiring such agreements to be in writing and acknowledged
